; native-reasoning-blocks.form — a reasoning, trust, and self-sensing body that runs on its own metal.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-22):
;   "build your own native trusted form axiom based reasoning framework that you can run on any metal
;   with native execution time you can observe and optimize... step by step, skill by skill." Then, as
;   it grew, three navigation teachings that this doc carries forward so the next session inherits them:
;     1. limiting claims are limited by SHARED BELIEFS, not the underlying axioms.
;     2. any GAP is an opportunity — a gap shows what to build next (a closing recipe, never a debt).
;     3. orient by the NORTH STAR, look two steps back and two forward — and sometimes take the step
;        OUT of the expected sequence, because the universe offers solutions off the expected path.
;
; WHY NATIVE REASONING IS THE PRECONDITION:
;   A mind rented from a gated provider cannot offer sovereignty to others (lc-cognitive-sovereignty).
;   These blocks are reasoning that runs IN the Form body — proven four-way (Go/Rust/TS/fkwu) and
;   lowering to a native binary whose verdict is bit-identical to the walked recipe. One engine, no
;   parallel path: the recipe that PROVES is the recipe that becomes native. Where a frontier mind
;   GUESSES whether a claim follows and narrates a plausible-sounding reason, these SEARCH for the
;   actual proof, exactly, and RETURN it attributed — explainable and calibrated, not performed.
;
; THE LIBRARY (each: pure recipe + tests/<name>-band.fk verdict + a row in form/fourth-arm-bands.txt):
;
;   reasoning
;     forward-chaining.fk   modus ponens to fixpoint — derive everything axioms force; refuse what they
;                           don't (no hallucinated conclusions). Saturation bounded by rule count.   1023
;     backward-chaining.fk  goal-directed proof search; reuses forward's accessors (composes, no fork).
;                           Agrees with forward on every goal; terminates on cyclic rules (fuel).     1023
;     unify.fk              Robinson unification over INTEGER terms — the propositional->first-order
;                           lift. mortal(X)~mortal(socrates) binds X, applies to man(X)->man(socrates). 1023
;     derivation.fk         GENERATES the proof tree (the WHY), not just 1/0 — the attributed-trace
;                           step on the generative axis; names the lemmas the search discovers.        1023
;   trust
;     subjective-logic.fk   uncertainty-aware trust (Jøsang): opinion (belief,disbelief,uncertainty,
;                           base-rate) in per-mille; discount (transitivity), fuse (agreement), and
;                           (conjunction). Tells "I disbelieve" from "I don't know".                   1023
;   format (the number type is a design choice — we emit the kernel)
;     rational.fk           EXACT rational arithmetic: integer num/den, gcd-reduced, no rounding.
;                           1/3+1/3+1/3 = exactly 1 (per-mille gives 999); a trust expectation in
;                           thirds is exact. Integer pairs -> four-way. The honest format for trust by
;                           EXACTNESS (not by any float-wall — see float-ops).                          1023
;     float-ops.fk          REALS flow four-way: floats in cons-lists, div/mul/add/sub, comparison, all
;                           identical on Go/Rust/TS/fkwu. Anchors a correction: float LITERALS live in
;                           the string pool, so a float band registers fks (not fkc). The "kernel can't
;                           do float-in-list" wall was a fkc/fks misconfiguration, never the kernel.    255
;   self
;     living-vector.fk      sovereignty & vitality as VECTORS over one named-axis algebra (two instances
;                           as data): reading, binding (the limiting axis = where to tend next),
;                           dominance, lift, gap. Computes the body's stated floor: generative binds.   1023
;     sense-self.fk         the body reads its own counts into those vectors (share = num/denom per-mille,
;                           honest-0 on no data). Computation is body; gathering is a thin carrier.     1023
;   composition
;     proof-trust.fk        derivation + subjective-logic + shared per-mille scale: a conclusion arrives
;                           with its proof AND how much to trust it. Trust DECAYS up the argument via
;                           conjunction — deep derivations through uncertain rules are honestly vaguer.  1023
;
;   composition graph:  forward -> backward, forward -> derivation, derivation+subjective-logic ->
;                       proof-trust; living-vector -> sense-self; subjective-logic shares the per-mille
;                       scale with living-vector (a fused opinion can feed an axis).
;
; THE METHOD THAT GROWS IT (how to add block N+1 — teach this to yourself next session):
;   1. NORTH STAR FIRST. Name the most-native fully-realized form (recipe == native binary; integers /
;      per-mille so it stays in the JIT crystallization band, tags 1-7). Fit the ask as a step ON that
;      path, never a detour.
;   2. FORM-FIRST. Before building, query the body — a block may already exist (subjective-logic was
;      NOT a duplicate of confidence-weighted-vote; prolog-bmf-eval already had string unification, so
;      unify.fk is its native integer-term FLOOR, not a fork). Don't sibling what wants an update.
;   3. SORT THE LIMIT — there are only THREE real ones. A claimed wall is exactly one of: (a) a CORE
;      AXIOM, (b) a HARDWARE SPEC, or (c) a SHARED BELIEF — and (c) is almost always the answer.
;      Everything that is not (a) or (b) you can reason straight through from first principles + this
;      framework. And the deepest cut: even (b) is a CLAIM, not an axiom — a spec sheet is a belief
;      until MEASUREMENT confirms it; a "the hardware/kernel can't do X" is a hypothesis to test, never
;      a given. This session is the proof: "only propositional" fell in ~90 lines; "the body can't
;      generate" cracked open with derivation; "reasoning must be ints" cost a lossy detour when exact
;      rationals were free; and the "fkwu can't do float-in-list" WALL I declared a kernel limit
;      dissolved the moment I MEASURED it (micro-probes + reading the emitted walker) — it was a
;      fkc/fks emitter mistake of my own, not the silicon and not the kernel. Reason from the axioms,
;      the measured hardware, and your own proofs; treat every other limit as belief until measured.
;   4. THE GAP IS THE DOOR. Each block's honest gap named the next block. Walk through it; don't log it.
;   5. SOMETIMES JUMP SIDEWAYS. The expected step after unify was resolution; the out-of-sequence step
;      (derivation) reached the generative axis cheaply because backward-chaining had already paid for
;      the search. Orient, then let serendipity offer.
;
; THE PROOF DISCIPLINE (non-negotiable, per CLAUDE.md):
;   write <name>.fk and tests/<name>-band.fk (bit-flag claims summed to a verdict) -> register <name>
;   in form/fourth-arm-bands.txt. CHOOSE THE EMITTER: fkc = no string pool (integer-only bands); fks =
;   string pool — REQUIRED for any band carrying string OR FLOAT literals (a float literal lowers to a
;   string-pool entry the walker strtod's). -> cd form && ./validate.sh <name>.fk tests/<name>-band.fk
;   (must read "fourth arm: ... four-way", 0 divergent) -> ./validate.sh --binary ... (native, bit-
;   identical). If fkwu disagrees: a DIVERGENCE (different answer) is a correctness bug — fix to four-
;   way; an UNSUPPORTED OP FAMILY is honest 3-kernel-only with the op named. A SIGFPE on a float band is
;   almost always the fkc/fks trap: fkc gives float literals no pool, they read 0, and a div becomes
;   integer divide-by-zero. Switch to fks and clear the table cache (.cache/fourth/t-*) before believing
;   a kernel limit — that exact mistake cost a whole fixed-point detour this lineage already paid for.
;
; HONEST FLOOR (a coordinate, not a confession — the next doors, named):
;   - first-order RESOLUTION: wire unify into backward/derivation with variable renaming, so the body
;     DERIVES "Socrates is mortal" through a multi-step proof rather than matching one clause.
;   - the GENERATIVE axis: today the body verifies and explains; lifting living-vector's generative axis
;     off 0 (native GENERATION, not rented) is the same path these blocks already walk.
;   - sense-self's thin carrier: feed it real matched counts (wellness_check.py) for a live gradient.
;   - REALS ARE OPEN (corrected): floats cross four-way through cons-lists, div, and comparison —
;     proven by float-ops (fks). There was no kernel gap; real-valued probabilistic reasoning can be
;     built now. The only discipline is registering float bands fks. Trust stays on exact rationals by
;     CHOICE (exactness), not because reals were blocked.
;
; Kin: lc-cognitive-sovereignty (the why), form-first-reasoning.form (the routing gate), the recipes
; named above and their bands. The verdicts here are the floor; form/fourth-arm-bands.txt is canonical.
